109typedef struct {
110 INT mem_off; /**< next offset in the memory arg area */
111 short retgrp; /**< return group # for a function */
112 /** function ret variable for return group -- there is a sub-table in the
113 finfo table which is indexed by the return group index (0 - retgrp_cnt-1).
114 This field is valid only for the sub-table. */
115 SPTR fval;
116 /** register descriptor for the case where the function is bind(C) and the
117 return value is a small structure returned in memory; 0 otherwise */
118 int ret_sm_struct;
119 int ret_align; /**< if returning small struct, this is its alignment */
120} finfo_t;

193/*
194 * Generating GSMOVE ILI is under XBIT(2,0x800000). When the XBIT is not
195 * set, _exp_smove() will proceed as before; in particular, chk_block() is
196 * called to add terminal ILI to the block current to the expander. When
197 * the XBIT is set, the GSMOVE ili are transformed sometime after the expander,
198 * but we still want the code in _exp_smove() to do the work. However, we
199 * cannot call chk_block() to add the terminal ILI; we must use 'addilt'.
200 * So, define and use a function pointer, p_chk_block, which calls either
201 * chk_block() or a new local addilit routine, gsmove_chk_block(). In this
202 * case, the current ilt is saved as the file static, gsmove_ilt.
203 */
204static void (*p_chk_block)(int) = chk_block;
205static void gsmove_chk_block(int);
206static int gsmove_ilt;
207
208/* aux.curr_entry->flags description:
209 * Initialized to 0 by exp_end
210 * NA 0x1 - need to save argument registers (set by exp_end).
211 * NA 0x2 - r1 is not needed (set by scheduler)
212 * NA 0x4 - function contained varargs or is passed memory arguments
213 * (set by exp_end)
214 * NA 0x8 - fast linkage
215 * 0x100 - must set up the frame (set by exp_end)
216 * 0x200 - AVX only: we can 32-byte align the stack if it is
217 * beneficial to do so (set by exp_end)
218 * 0x400 - AVX only: we MUST 32-byte align the stack, e.g. because
219 * a 32-byte aligned load or store has been generated
220 * which assumes that the stack is 32-byte aligned.
221 * 0x40000000 - mscall seen
222 * 0x80000000 - alloca called.
223 */
224
225int
226is_passbyval_dummy(int sptr)
227{
228 if (BYVALDEFAULT(GBL_CURRFUNC))
229 return 1;
230 if (PASSBYVALG(sptr))
231 return 1;
232 return 0;
233}

235/* Visual Studio cDEC$ ATTRIBUTES are very specific about when a character
236 argument is passed by value, passed by ref with a length, passed
237 by ref without a length. This routine returns true if the argument
238 is pass by reference with a length
239 */
240int
241needlen(int sym, int func)
242{
243 if (sym <= 0)
244 return false;
245
246 if (func <= 0)
247 return false;
248
249 if (sym == FVALG(func)) {
250
251 /* special case for functions returning character :
252 always need a length This can not be modified
253 any ATTRIBUTES.
254 */
255 return true;
256 }
257
258 if (PASSBYVALG(sym)) {
259 return false;
260 }
261 if (STDCALLG(func) || CFUNCG(func)) {
262 if (PASSBYREFG(sym)) {
263 return false;
264 }
265
266 if (PASSBYREFG(func)) {
267 return true;
268 }
269
270 /* plain func= c/stdcall is pass by value */
271 return false;
272 }
273 return true;
274}

276static void
277create_llvm_display_temp(void)
278{
279 DTYPE dtype;
280 SPTR display_temp, asym;
281
282 if (!gbl.internal)
283 return;
284
285 display_temp = getccsym('S', expb.gentmps++, ST_VAR);
286
287 if (gbl.outlined) {
288 SCP(display_temp, SC_PRIVATE);
289 if (gbl.internal >= 1)
290 load_uplevel_addresses(display_temp);
291 } else if (gbl.internal == 1) {
292 dtype = DTYPEG(display_temp);
293 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_STRUCT)
294 dtype = make_uplevel_arg_struct();
295 DTYPEP(display_temp, dtype);
296 SCP(display_temp, SC_LOCAL);
297 ADDRTKNP(display_temp, 1);
298 sym_is_refd(display_temp);
299 aux.curr_entry->display = display_temp;
300
301 if (!gbl.outlined) {
302 /* now load address of local variable on to this array */
303 load_uplevel_addresses(display_temp);
304 }
305 return;
306 } else {
307 SCP(display_temp, SC_DUMMY);
308 dtype = DTYPEG(display_temp);
309 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_STRUCT)
310 dtype = make_uplevel_arg_struct();
311 asym = mk_argasym(display_temp);
312 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(display_temp)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
313 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
314 }
315 DTYPEP(display_temp, DT_ADDR);
316 sym_is_refd(display_temp);
317 aux.curr_entry->display = display_temp;
318}

322/**
323 * Expand entry, main, sub, or func. For an unnamed program, PROGRAM,
324 * SUBROUTINE, or FUNCTION, sym is 0; otherwise, sym is the ENTRY name.
325 */
326void
327exp_header(SPTR sym)
328{
329 if (sym == SPTR_NULL) {
330 smove_flag = 0;
331 mscall_flag = 0;
332 if (WINNT_CALL)
333 mscall_flag = 1;
334 alloca_flag = 0;
335 sym = gbl.currsub;
336 allocharhdr = SPTR_NULL;
337 memarg_var = SPTR_NULL;
338 expb.arglcnt.next = expb.arglcnt.start = expb.arglcnt.max;
339 aux.curr_entry->ent_save = SPTR_NULL;
340 if (gbl.rutype != RU_PROG) {
341 if ((!WINNT_CALL && !CREFG(sym)) || NOMIXEDSTRLENG(sym))
342 pp_entries();
343 else
344 pp_entries_mixedstrlen();
345 }
346 mkrtemp_init();
347 } else {
348 if (flg.smp && OUTLINEDG(sym) && BIHNUMG(sym)) {
349 return;
350 }
351 flsh_block();
352 cr_block();
353 }
354
355 /* get expb.curbih for this entry and save in symtab */
356
357 BIHNUMP(sym, expb.curbih);
358
359 /* generate ILI for entry operator */
360
361 expb.curilt = addilt(0, ad1ili(IL_ENTRY, sym));
362 /*
363 * Store into the bih for this block the entry ST item and define
364 * the pointer to the auxilary Entry information and the BIH index
365 * for the current function.
366 */
367 BIH_LABEL(expb.curbih) = sym;
368#ifdef OUTLINEDG
369 gbl.outlined = ((OUTLINEDG(sym)) ? true : false);
370#endif
371
372 if (sym == gbl.currsub)
373 reg_init(sym); /* init reg info and set stb.curr_entry */
374 if (gbl.internal >= 1) {
375 /* always create display variable for gbl.internal */
376 create_llvm_display_temp();
377 }
378
379 if (gbl.outlined) {
380 SPTR asym;
381 int ili_uplevel;
382 SPTR tmpuplevel;
383 int nme, ili;
384 bihb.parfg = 1;
385 aux.curr_entry->uplevel = ll_get_shared_arg(sym);
386 asym = mk_argasym(aux.curr_entry->uplevel);
387 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(aux.curr_entry->uplevel)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
388 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
389
390 /* if I am the task_routine(arg1, task*) */
391 if (TASKFNG(sym)) {
392 bihb.taskfg = 1;
393
394 /* Set up local variable and store the address where first shared
395 * variable is stored.
396 */
397 tmpuplevel = getccsym('S', expb.gentmps++, ST_VAR);
398 SCP(tmpuplevel, SC_PRIVATE);
399 DTYPEP(tmpuplevel, DT_ADDR);
400 sym_is_refd(tmpuplevel);
401 ENCLFUNCP(tmpuplevel, GBL_CURRFUNC);
402
403 /* aux.curr_entry->uplevel = arg2[0] */
404 /* 2 levels of indirection.
405 * 1st: Fortran specific where we load address of
406 * argument from address constant variable.
407 * We store the address of argument into
408 * address constant at the beginning of routine.
409 * We should one day revisit if it is applicable anymore.
410 * Or if we should just do the same as C.
411 * We would now have an address of task
412 * 2nd: Load first element from task which should be the
413 * address on task_sptr where first shared var address
414 * is stored.
415 */
416 ili_uplevel = mk_address(aux.curr_entry->uplevel);
417 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, asym, 0, 0);
418 ili_uplevel = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili_uplevel, nme); /* .Cxxx = (task) */
419 nme = addnme(NT_IND, aux.curr_entry->uplevel, nme, 0);
420 ili_uplevel = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili_uplevel, nme); /* taskptr = .Cxxx */
421
422 ili = ad_acon(tmpuplevel, 0);
423 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, tmpuplevel, 0, 0);
424 ili = ad3ili(IL_STA, ili_uplevel, ili, nme);
425 chk_block(ili);
426 aux.curr_entry->uplevel = tmpuplevel;
427 }
428 } else if (ISTASKDUPG(sym)) {
429 SPTR asym;
430 int ili_uplevel;
431 SPTR tmpuplevel;
432 int nme, ili;
433 aux.curr_entry->uplevel = ll_get_hostprog_arg(sym, 2);
434 asym = mk_argasym(aux.curr_entry->uplevel);
435 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(aux.curr_entry->uplevel)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
436 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
437
438 bihb.taskfg = 1;
439
440 /* Set up local variable and store the address of shared variable
441 * from second argument: taskdup(nexttask, task, lastitr)
442 * So that we don't need to do multiple indirect access when
443 * we want to access shared variable.
444 */
445 tmpuplevel = getccsym('S', expb.gentmps++, ST_VAR);
446 SCP(tmpuplevel, SC_PRIVATE);
447 DTYPEP(tmpuplevel, DT_ADDR);
448 sym_is_refd(tmpuplevel);
449 ENCLFUNCP(tmpuplevel, GBL_CURRFUNC);
450
451 /* now load address from arg2[0] to tmpuplevel */
452 ili_uplevel = mk_address(aux.curr_entry->uplevel);
453 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, asym, 0, 0);
454
455 /* 2 levels of indirection.
456 * 1st: Fortran specific where we load address of
457 * argument from address constant variable.
458 * We store the address of argument into
459 * address constant at the beginning of routine.
460 * We should one day revisit if it is applicable anymore.
461 * Or if we should just do the same as C.
462 * We would now have an address of task
463 * 2nd: Load first element from task which should be the
464 * address on task_sptr where the first shared var
465 * address is stored.
466 */
467 ili_uplevel = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili_uplevel, nme); /* .Cxxx = (task) */
468 nme = addnme(NT_IND, aux.curr_entry->uplevel, nme, 0);
469 ili_uplevel = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili_uplevel, nme); /* taskptr = .Cxxx */
470
471 ili = ad_acon(tmpuplevel, 0);
472 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, tmpuplevel, 0, 0);
473 ili = ad3ili(IL_STA, ili_uplevel, ili, nme);
474 chk_block(ili);
475 aux.curr_entry->uplevel = tmpuplevel;
476 } else {
477 bihb.parfg = 0;
478 bihb.taskfg = 0;
479 aux.curr_entry->uplevel = SPTR_NULL;
480 }
481
482 BIH_EN(expb.curbih) = 1;
483 gbl.entbih = expb.curbih;
484 if (gbl.rutype != RU_PROG) {
485 if ((!WINNT_CALL && !CREFG(sym)) || NOMIXEDSTRLENG(sym))
486 pp_params(sym);
487 else
488 pp_params_mixedstrlen(sym);
489 }
490
491 if (gbl.internal && gbl.outlined && aux.curr_entry->display) {
492 /* do this after aux->curr_entry.display is created: */
493 int ili_uplevel;
494 int nme;
495 int ili = ad_acon(aux.curr_entry->display, 0);
496 aux.curr_entry->uplevel = ll_get_shared_arg(sym);
497 ili_uplevel = mk_address(aux.curr_entry->uplevel);
498 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, aux.curr_entry->uplevel, 0, 0);
499 ili_uplevel = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili_uplevel, nme);
500 ili_uplevel = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili_uplevel,
501 addnme(NT_IND, aux.curr_entry->display, nme, 0));
502 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, addnme(NT_IND, aux.curr_entry->display, nme, 0));
503 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, aux.curr_entry->display, 0, 0);
504 ili = ad3ili(IL_STA, ili_uplevel, ili, nme);
505 chk_block(ili);
506 flg.recursive = true;
507 }
508 if (flg.debug || XBIT(120, 0x1000) || XBIT(123, 0x400)) {
509 /*
510 * Since the debug code is produced, the entry block will have
511 * line number of 0. The block following the entry block will
512 * have the entry's line number. This block represents the entry
513 * to the function as seen by the debugger.
514 */
515 BIH_LINENO(expb.curbih) = 0;
516 wr_block();
517 cr_block();
518 BIH_LINENO(expb.curbih) = gbl.lineno;
519 } else {
520 wr_block(); /* make entry block separate */
521 cr_block();
522 }
523}

525/*
526 * WARNING: there are nomixedstrlen and mixedstrlen functions to preprocess
527 * entries.
528 */
529static void
530pp_entries(void)
531{
532 int func;
533 int nargs;
534 int *dpdscp;
535 int sym;
536 int curpos;
537 int pos;
538 int lenpos;
539 int argpos;
540 int finfox;
541 int byvalue;
542 /*
543 * Preprocess the entries in the subprogram to determine for which
544 * entries arguments must be copied due to the arguments occupying
545 * different positions. The entry and the arguments which must
546 * be copied are flagged (COPYPRMS flag). Also, for a character
547 * argument whose length is passed, a symbol table entry is created
548 * to represent its length (the arg's CLEN field will locate the length
549 * ST item).
550 *
551 * A unique list (table) is created (located by parg) of the arguments
552 * and lengths for character arguments which appear in all of the entries.
553 * While a function is processed, a section of the table is divided into
554 * two tables: the first table is used for the arguments and the second
555 * table is used for lengths. argpos is an index into the table and
556 * locates the position of the most recent unique argument; lenpos indicates
557 * the position of the most recent character length.
558 *
559 * Note that the ADDRESS field is temporarily used to record the
560 * argument's position in the list created for all the arguments.
561 * An argument is entered into the list only once even though it
562 * may occur in more than one entry.
563 */
564
565 /* compute number of entries and total number of arguments */
566 finfox = retgrp_cnt = nentries = nargs = 0;
567 for (func = gbl.entries; func != NOSYM; func = SYMLKG(func)) {
568 nargs += PARAMCTG(func);
569 nentries++;
570 }
571 /*
572 * assume all arguments are character arguments; note that the first
573 * argument is in position 1. Allocate space for the table used to
574 * record arguments and lengths and space for the finfo table (to be
575 * used by pp_params).
576 */
577 nargs = 2 * nargs + 1;
578 parg = (int *)getitem(1, sizeof(int) * nargs);
579
580 pfinfo = (finfo_t *)getitem(1, sizeof(finfo_t) * nentries);
581 BZERO(pfinfo, finfo_t, nentries);
582
583 argpos = 0;
584 for (func = gbl.entries; func != NOSYM; func = SYMLKG(func)) {
585 int savlenpos, i, total_words;
586
587 total_words = 0;
588 MIDNUMP(func, finfox++); /* remember index to func's finfo */
589 nargs = PARAMCTG(func);
590 dpdscp = (int *)(aux.dpdsc_base + DPDSCG(func));
591 curpos = 0;
592 if (gbl.rutype != RU_FUNC)
593 goto scan_args;
594 /*
595 * enter the function return variable into the group return table
596 * (table is shared with the finfo table) if not already there.
597 */
598 for (i = 0; i < retgrp_cnt; i++)
599 if (pfinfo[i].fval == FVALG(func)) {
600 pfinfo[MIDNUMG(func)].retgrp = i;
601 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
602 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s shares group %d\n", SYMNAME(func), i);
603 goto check_type;
604 }
605 pfinfo[retgrp_cnt].fval = FVALG(func);
606 pfinfo[MIDNUMG(func)].retgrp = retgrp_cnt;
607 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
608 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s enters group %d, %s\n", SYMNAME(func), retgrp_cnt,
609 SYMNAME(FVALG(func)));
610 retgrp_cnt++;
611
612 check_type:
613 switch (DTY(DTYPEG(func))) {
614 case TY_CHAR:
615 case TY_NCHAR:
616 /* NOTE: if function returns char, then all entries return char
617 */
618 if (func == gbl.currsub) {
619 sym = dpdscp[nargs - 1];
620 parg[1] = sym;
621 if (needlen(sym, func) &&
622 (DTYPEG(func) == DT_ASSCHAR || DTYPEG(func) == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
623 DTYPEG(func) == DT_DEFERNCHAR || DTYPEG(func) == DT_ASSNCHAR)) {
624 int clen = CLENG(sym);
625 if (clen == 0 || !REDUCG(clen)) {
626 clen = getdumlen();
627 CLENP(sym, clen);
628 }
629 parg[2] = clen;
630 ADDRESSP(clen, 2);
631 } else
632 parg[2] = -sym;
633 ADDRESSP(sym, 1);
634 argpos = 2;
635 }
636 curpos = 2;
637 nargs--;
638 total_words += 2;
639 break;
640 case TY_CMPLX:
641 case TY_DCMPLX:
642#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
643 case TY_QCMPLX:
644#endif
645 /* for complex functions, an extra argument is the first argument
646 * which is also used to return the result.
647 */
648 if (CFUNCG(func) || CMPLXFUNC_C) {
649 break;
650 }
651 curpos = 1;
652 sym = dpdscp[nargs - 1];
653 pos = ADDRESSG(sym) & 0xffff;
654 if (pos == 0) {
655 parg[++argpos] = sym;
656 ADDRESSP(sym, argpos);
657 pos = argpos;
658 }
659 if (pos != curpos) {
660 COPYPRMSP(func, 1);
661 COPYPRMSP(sym, 1);
662 }
663 nargs--;
664 total_words++;
665 break;
666 default:
667 break;
668 }
669
670 scan_args:
671 savlenpos = lenpos = argpos + nargs;
672
673 while (nargs--) {
674 int osym;
675 DTYPE dt;
676 curpos++;
677 sym = *dpdscp;
678 osym = sym;
679
680 if (((DTY(DTYPEG(sym))) == TY_STRUCT) ||
681 ((DTY(DTYPEG(sym))) == TY_ARRAY) || ((DTY(DTYPEG(sym))) == TY_UNION))
682 /* no passbyvalue arrays, structs */
683 byvalue = 0;
684 else
685 byvalue = BYVALDEFAULT(func);
686
687 if (PASSBYVALG(sym))
688 byvalue = 1;
689 if (PASSBYREFG(sym))
690 byvalue = 0;
691
692 if (SCG(sym) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sym) && XBIT(57, 0x80000) &&
693 SCG(MIDNUMG(sym)) == SC_DUMMY) {
694 /* for char, we put pointee in argument list so as to get
695 * the char length here, but we really pass the pointer
696 * use the actual pointer */
697 sym = MIDNUMG(sym);
698 }
699 dpdscp++;
700 pos = ADDRESSG(sym) & 0xffff;
701 if (pos == 0) {
702 parg[++argpos] = sym;
703 ADDRESSP(sym, argpos);
704 pos = argpos;
705 }
706 if (pos != curpos) {
707 COPYPRMSP(func, 1);
708 COPYPRMSP(sym, 1);
709 }
710 total_words++;
711 dt = DDTG(DTYPEG(osym));
712
713 if (byvalue) {
714 if (DTY(dt) == TY_DBLE || DTY(dt) == TY_INT8 || DTY(dt) == TY_LOG8 ||
715 DTY(dt) == TY_CMPLX)
716 total_words++;
717 else if (DTY(dt) == TY_DCMPLX || DTY(dt) == TY_QUAD)
718 total_words += 3;
719 else if ((DTY(dt) == TY_STRUCT && (size_of(DTYPEG(osym)) > 4)) || DTY(dt) == TY_QCMPLX)
720 total_words += size_of(DTYPEG(osym)) / 4 - 1;
721 }
722
723 /*
724 * save length if character
725 */
726 if ((DTYG(DTYPEG(osym)) == TY_CHAR || DTYG(DTYPEG(osym)) == TY_NCHAR) &&
727 needlen(osym, func)) {
728 parg[++lenpos] = osym;
729 total_words++;
730 }
731 }
732 /*
733 * all arguments have been processed for func; process the lengths
734 * which have been saved in the table. Since there could be a gap
735 * between the arguments and the lengths, the lengths which are seen
736 * for the first time are moved up to follow the arguments.
737 */
738 while (savlenpos < lenpos) {
739 int osym;
740
741 savlenpos++;
742 curpos++;
743 sym = parg[savlenpos];
744 osym = sym;
745 if (SCG(sym) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sym) && XBIT(57, 0x80000) &&
746 SCG(MIDNUMG(sym)) == SC_DUMMY) {
747 /* for char, we put pointee in argument list so as to get
748 * the char length here, but we really pass the pointer
749 * use the actual pointer */
750 sym = MIDNUMG(sym);
751 }
752 pos = (ADDRESSG(sym) >> 16) & 0xffff;
753 if (pos == 0) {
754 ++argpos;
755 ADDRESSP(sym, argpos << 16 | ADDRESSG(sym));
756 if (needlen(sym, func) && (DDTG(DTYPEG(osym)) == DT_ASSCHAR ||
757 DDTG(DTYPEG(osym)) == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
758 DDTG(DTYPEG(osym)) == DT_DEFERNCHAR ||
759 DDTG(DTYPEG(osym)) == DT_ASSNCHAR)) {
760 int clen;
761 clen = CLENG(osym);
762 if (clen == 0) {
763 clen = getdumlen();
764 CLENP(osym, clen);
765 parg[argpos] = clen;
766 } else if (REDUCG(clen)) {
767 parg[argpos] = clen;
768 } else {
769 /* adjustable length dummy */
770 parg[argpos] = -sym;
771 AUTOBJP(osym, 1); /* mark as adjustable length */
772 }
773 } else
774 parg[argpos] = -sym;
775 pos = argpos;
776 }
777 if (pos != curpos &&
778 (DDTG(DTYPEG(osym)) == DT_ASSCHAR ||
779 DDTG(DTYPEG(osym)) == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
780 DDTG(DTYPEG(osym)) == DT_DEFERNCHAR ||
781 DDTG(DTYPEG(osym)) == DT_ASSNCHAR)
782 && !AUTOBJG(osym)
783 ) {
784 sym = CLENG(osym);
785#if DEBUG
786 assert(sym != 0, "pp_entries: 0 clen", parg[savlenpos], ERR_Severe);
787#endif
788 parg[pos] = sym;
789 COPYPRMSP(sym, 1);
790 COPYPRMSP(func, 1);
791 }
792 }
793#if defined(TARGET_WIN)
794 if (MSCALLG(func)) {
795 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
796 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s total_words %d\n", SYMNAME(func), total_words);
797 if (total_words > 0) {
798 ARGSIZEP(func, total_words * 4);
799 } else if (total_words == 0)
800 ARGSIZEP(func, -1);
801 }
802#endif
803 }
804 for (pos = 1; pos <= argpos; pos++) {
805 sym = parg[pos];
806 if (sym > 0) {
807 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
808 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%4d: %s %s\n", pos, SYMNAME(sym),
809 COPYPRMSG(sym) ? "<copied>" : "");
810 ADDRESSP(sym, 0);
811 } else if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
812 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%4d: length of %s\n", pos, SYMNAME(-sym));
813 }
814
815 if (retgrp_cnt > 1) {
816 retgrp_var = getccsym('F', 0, ST_VAR);
817 SCP(retgrp_var, SC_LOCAL);
818 DTYPEP(retgrp_var, DT_INT);
819 }
820}
821
822/*
823 * WARNING: there are nomixedstrlen and mixedstrlen functions to preprocess
824 * entries.
825 */
826static void
827pp_entries_mixedstrlen(void)
828{
829 int func;
830 int nargs;
831 int *dpdscp;
832 SPTR sym;
833 int curpos;
834 int pos;
835 int argpos;
836 int finfox;
837 int byvalue = 0;
838 /*
839 * Preprocess the entries in the subprogram to determine for which
840 * entries arguments must be copied due to the arguments occupying
841 * different positions. The entry and the arguments which must
842 * be copied are flagged (COPYPRMS flag). Also, for a character
843 * argument whose length is passed, a symbol table entry is created
844 * to represent its length (the arg's CLEN field will locate the length
845 * ST item).
846 *
847 * A unique list (table) is created (located by parg) of the arguments
848 * and lengths for character arguments which appear in all of the entries.
849 * While a function is processed, a section of the table is divided into
850 * two tables: the first table is used for the arguments and the second
851 * table is used for lengths. argpos is an index into the table and
852 * locates the position of the most recent unique argument; lenpos indicates
853 * the position of the most recent character length.
854 *
855 * Note that the ADDRESS field is temporarily used to record the
856 * argument's position in the list created for all the arguments.
857 * An argument is entered into the list only once even though it
858 * may occur in more than one entry.
859 */
860
861 /* compute number of entries and total number of arguments */
862 finfox = retgrp_cnt = nentries = nargs = 0;
863 for (func = gbl.entries; func != NOSYM; func = SYMLKG(func)) {
864 nargs += PARAMCTG(func);
865 nentries++;
866 }
867 if (nentries > 1) {
868 sym = getccsym('Q', expb.gentmps++, ST_VAR);
869 SCP(sym, SC_LOCAL);
870 DTYPEP(sym, DT_INT);
871 aux.curr_entry->ent_save = sym;
872 ADDRTKNP(sym, 1); /* so optimizer won't delete */
873 }
874 /*
875 * assume all arguments are character arguments; note that the first
876 * argument is in position 1. Allocate space for the table used to
877 * record arguments and lengths and space for the finfo table (to be
878 * used by pp_params).
879 */
880 nargs = 2 * nargs + 1;
881 parg = (int *)getitem(1, sizeof(int) * nargs);
882
883 pfinfo = (finfo_t *)getitem(1, sizeof(finfo_t) * nentries);
884 BZERO(pfinfo, finfo_t, nentries);
885
886 argpos = 0;
887 for (func = gbl.entries; func != NOSYM; func = SYMLKG(func)) {
888 int i, total_words;
889
890 total_words = 0;
891 MIDNUMP(func, finfox++); /* remember index to func's finfo */
892 nargs = PARAMCTG(func);
893 dpdscp = (int *)(aux.dpdsc_base + DPDSCG(func));
894 curpos = 0;
895 if (gbl.rutype != RU_FUNC)
896 goto scan_args;
897 /*
898 * enter the function return variable into the group return table
899 * (table is shared with the finfo table) if not already there.
900 */
901 for (i = 0; i < retgrp_cnt; i++)
902 if (pfinfo[i].fval == FVALG(func)) {
903 pfinfo[MIDNUMG(func)].retgrp = i;
904 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
905 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s shares group %d\n", SYMNAME(func), i);
906 goto check_type;
907 }
908 pfinfo[retgrp_cnt].fval = FVALG(func);
909 pfinfo[MIDNUMG(func)].retgrp = retgrp_cnt;
910 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
911 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s enters group %d, %s\n", SYMNAME(func), retgrp_cnt,
912 SYMNAME(FVALG(func)));
913 retgrp_cnt++;
914
915 check_type:
916 switch (DTY(DTYPEG(func))) {
917 case TY_CHAR:
918 case TY_NCHAR:
919 /* NOTE: if function returns char, then all entries return char
920 */
921 if (func == gbl.currsub) {
922 sym = convertSPTR(dpdscp[nargs - 1]);
923 parg[1] = sym;
924 if ((DTYPEG(func) == DT_ASSCHAR || DTYPEG(func) == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
925 DTYPEG(func) == DT_DEFERNCHAR || DTYPEG(func) == DT_ASSNCHAR)) {
926 int clen = CLENG(sym);
927 if (clen == 0 || !REDUCG(clen)) {
928 clen = getdumlen();
929 CLENP(sym, clen);
930 }
931 parg[2] = CLENG(sym);
932 ADDRESSP(parg[2], 2);
933 } else
934 parg[2] = -sym;
935 ADDRESSP(sym, 1);
936 argpos = 2;
937 }
938 curpos = 2;
939 nargs--;
940 total_words++;
941 /* character length */
942 if (needlen(sym, func)) {
943 total_words++;
944 }
945
946 break;
947 case TY_CMPLX:
948 case TY_DCMPLX:
949 /* for complex functions, an extra argument is the first argument
950 * which is also used to return the result.
951 */
952 curpos = 1;
953 sym = convertSPTR(dpdscp[nargs - 1]);
954 pos = ADDRESSG(sym) & 0xffff;
955 if (pos == 0) {
956 parg[++argpos] = sym;
957 ADDRESSP(sym, argpos);
958 pos = argpos;
959 }
960 if (pos != curpos) {
961 COPYPRMSP(func, 1);
962 COPYPRMSP(sym, 1);
963 }
964 nargs--;
965 total_words++;
966 break;
967 default:
968 break;
969 }
970
971 scan_args:
972 while (nargs--) {
973 int osym;
974 DTYPE dt;
975 curpos++;
976 sym = convertSPTR(*dpdscp);
977 osym = sym;
978
979 if (((DTY(DTYPEG(sym))) == TY_STRUCT) ||
980 ((DTY(DTYPEG(sym))) == TY_ARRAY) || ((DTY(DTYPEG(sym))) == TY_UNION))
981 /* no passbyvalue arrays, structs */
982 byvalue = 0;
983 else
984 byvalue = BYVALDEFAULT(func);
985
986 if (PASSBYVALG(sym))
987 byvalue = 1;
988 if (PASSBYREFG(sym))
989 byvalue = 0;
990
991 if (SCG(sym) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sym) && XBIT(57, 0x80000) &&
992 SCG(MIDNUMG(sym)) == SC_DUMMY) {
993 /* char pointers, we put the pointee on the argument
994 * list so as to get the char length, but we really pass
995 * the pointer.
996 * replace by the actual pointer */
997 sym = MIDNUMG(sym);
998 }
999 dpdscp++;
1000 pos = ADDRESSG(sym) & 0xffff;
1001 if (pos == 0) {
1002 parg[++argpos] = sym;
1003 ADDRESSP(sym, argpos);
1004 pos = argpos;
1005 }
1006 if (pos != curpos) {
1007 COPYPRMSP(func, 1);
1008 COPYPRMSP(sym, 1);
1009 }
1010 total_words++;
1011 dt = DDTG(DTYPEG(osym));
1012
1013 if (byvalue) {
1014 if (DTY(dt) == TY_DBLE || DTY(dt) == TY_INT8 || DTY(dt) == TY_LOG8 ||
1015 DTY(dt) == TY_CMPLX)
1016 total_words++;
1017 else if (DTY(dt) == TY_DCMPLX || DTY(dt) == TY_QUAD)
1018 total_words += 3;
1019 else if ((DTY(dt) == TY_STRUCT && (size_of(DTYPEG(osym)) > 4)) || DTY(dt) == TY_QCMPLX)
1020 total_words += size_of(DTYPEG(osym)) / 4 - 1;
1021 }
1022
1023 /*
1024 * save length if character
1025 */
1026 if (DTY(dt) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dt) == TY_NCHAR) {
1027 curpos++;
1028 pos = (ADDRESSG(sym) >> 16) & 0xffff;
1029 if (pos == 0) {
1030 pos = ++argpos;
1031 ADDRESSP(sym, argpos << 16 | ADDRESSG(sym));
1032 if (needlen(sym, func) &&
1033 (dt == DT_ASSCHAR || dt == DT_ASSNCHAR || dt == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
1034 dt == DT_DEFERNCHAR)) {
1035 int clen;
1036 clen = CLENG(osym);
1037 if (clen == 0) {
1038 clen = getdumlen();
1039 CLENP(osym, clen);
1040 parg[argpos] = CLENG(osym);
1041 } else if (REDUCG(clen)) {
1042 parg[argpos] = clen;
1043 } else {
1044 /* adjustable length dummy */
1045 parg[argpos] = -sym;
1046 AUTOBJP(osym, 1); /* mark as adjustable length */
1047 }
1048 } else
1049 parg[argpos] = -sym;
1050 }
1051 if (pos != curpos &&
1052 (dt == DT_ASSCHAR || dt == DT_ASSNCHAR || dt == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
1053 dt == DT_DEFERNCHAR)
1054 && !AUTOBJG(osym)
1055 ) {
1056 sym = CLENG(osym);
1057#if DEBUG
1058 assert(sym != 0, "pp_entries_mixedstrlen: 0 clen", parg[pos],
1059 ERR_Severe);
1060#endif
1061 COPYPRMSP(sym, 1);
1062 COPYPRMSP(func, 1);
1063 }
1064 if (needlen(sym, func)) {
1065 total_words++;
1066 }
1067 }
1068 }
1069 if (WINNT_CALL) {
1070 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1071 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s total_words %d\n", SYMNAME(func), total_words);
1072 if (total_words > 0) {
1073 ARGSIZEP(func, total_words * 4);
1074 } else if (total_words == 0)
1075 ARGSIZEP(func, -1);
1076 }
1077 }
1078 for (pos = 1; pos <= argpos; pos++) {
1079 sym = convertSPTR(parg[pos]);
1080 if (sym > 0) {
1081 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1082 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%4d: %s %s\n", pos, SYMNAME(sym),
1083 COPYPRMSG(sym) ? "<copied>" : "");
1084 ADDRESSP(sym, 0);
1085 } else if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1086 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%4d: length of %s\n", pos, SYMNAME(-sym));
1087 }
1088
1089 if (retgrp_cnt > 1) {
1090 retgrp_var = getccsym('F', 0, ST_VAR);
1091 SCP(retgrp_var, SC_LOCAL);
1092 DTYPEP(retgrp_var, DT_INT);
1093 }
1094}

1096SPTR
1097getdumlen(void)
1098{
1099 SPTR sym = getccsym('U', expb.chardtmps++, ST_VAR);
1100 if (CHARLEN_64BIT) {
1101 DTYPEP(sym, DT_INT8);
1102 } else {
1103 DTYPEP(sym, DT_INT);
1104 }
1105 SCP(sym, SC_DUMMY);
1106 REDUCP(sym, 1); /* mark temp as char len dummy */
1107 PASSBYVALP(sym, 1); /* Char len dummies are passed by value */
1108 return sym;
1109}

1111SPTR
1112gethost_dumlen(int arg, ISZ_T address)
1113{
1114 SPTR sym = getccsym('U', arg, ST_VAR);
1115 if (CHARLEN_64BIT) {
1116 DTYPEP(sym, DT_INT8);
1117 } else {
1118 DTYPEP(sym, DT_INT);
1119 }
1120 SCP(sym, SC_DUMMY);
1121 ADDRESSP(sym, address);
1122 REDUCP(sym, 1); /* mark temp as char len dummy */
1123 UPLEVELP(sym, 1);
1124 PASSBYVALP(sym, 1);
1125 pop_sym(sym); /* don't let this symbol conflict with getdumlen() */
1126 return sym;
1127}

1129static int
1130exp_type_bound_proc_call(int arg, SPTR descno, int vtoff, int arglnk)
1131{
1132
1133 SPTR sym;
1134 int ili;
1135 int type_offset, vft_offset, func_offset, sz;
1136 int jsra_mscall_flag;
1137
1138 sym = descno;
1139
1140 if (XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
1141 type_offset = 72;
1142 vft_offset = 80;
1143 } else {
1144 type_offset = 40;
1145 vft_offset = 48;
1146 }
1147 func_offset = 8 * (vtoff - 1);
1148 sz = MSZ_I8;
1149 ADDRTKNP(sym, 1);
1150 if (SCG(sym) == SC_EXTERN) {
1151 int ili2;
1152 SPTR tmp = getccsym_sc('Q', expb.gentmps++, ST_VAR, SC_LOCAL);
1153
1154 DTYPEP(tmp, DT_ADDR);
1155
1156 ili = ad1ili(IL_ACON, get_acon(sym, 0));
1157
1158 ili2 = ad1ili(IL_ACON, get_acon(tmp, 0));
1159
1160 ili = ad3ili(IL_STA, ili, ili2, NME_UNK);
1161 chk_block(ili);
1162
1163 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili2, NME_UNK);
1164 ili = ad3ili(IL_AADD, ili, ad_aconi(vft_offset), 0);
1165 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, NME_UNK);
1166 ili = ad3ili(IL_AADD, ili, ad_aconi(func_offset), 0);
1167 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, NME_UNK);
1168 } else if (SCG(sym) != SC_DUMMY) {
1169 ili = mk_address(sym);
1170 ili = ad3ili(IL_AADD, ili, ad_aconi(type_offset), 0);
1171 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, NME_UNK);
1172 ili = ad3ili(IL_AADD, ili, ad_aconi(vft_offset), 0);
1173 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, NME_UNK);
1174 ili = ad3ili(IL_AADD, ili, ad_aconi(func_offset), 0);
1175 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, NME_UNK);
1176 } else {
1177 if (!TASKDUPG(gbl.currsub) && CONTAINEDG(gbl.currsub) && INTERNREFG(sym)) {
1178 ili = mk_address(sym);
1179 } else {
1180 const SPTR asym = mk_argasym(sym);
1181 const int addr = mk_address(sym);
1182 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, addr, addnme(NT_VAR, asym, 0, 0));
1183 }
1184 ili = ad3ili(IL_AADD, ili, ad_aconi(type_offset), 0);
1185 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, NME_UNK);
1186 ili = ad3ili(IL_AADD, ili, ad_aconi(vft_offset), 0);
1187 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, NME_UNK);
1188 ili = ad3ili(IL_AADD, ili, ad_aconi(func_offset), 0);
1189 ili = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ili, NME_UNK);
1190 }
1191
1192 if (!MSCALLG(arg))
1193 jsra_mscall_flag = 0;
1194 else
1195 jsra_mscall_flag = 0x1;
1196
1197 return ad4ili(IL_JSRA, ili, arglnk, jsra_mscall_flag, fptr_iface);
1198}

1202has_desc_arg(int func, int sptr)

1217
1218static int
1219check_desc(int func, int sptr)
1220{
1221 /* Called by check_desc_args() below. Swaps traditional descriptor arguments
1222 * with type descriptor arguments when they're out of order.
1223 */
1224
1225 int nargs, *dpdscp, desc, *scratch;
1226 int pos, pos2, pos3, argsym, i, seenCC, seenDesc, seenSym, seenClass;
1227 int swap_from, swap_to, j, pos4, rslt;
1228
1229 rslt = 0;
1230 desc = SDSCG(sptr);
1231 if (!desc)
1232 return 0;
1233
1234 dpdscp = (int *)(aux.dpdsc_base + DPDSCG(func));
1235 nargs = PARAMCTG(func);
1236
1237 for (seenSym = seenDesc = seenCC = seenClass = pos = pos2 = pos3 = pos4 = i =
1238 0;
1239 i < nargs; ++i) {
1240 argsym = dpdscp[i];
1241
1242 if (!seenSym &&
1243 (!SDSCG(argsym) || (SCG(SDSCG(argsym)) != SC_DUMMY &&
1244 (!CLASSG(argsym) || FVALG(func) == argsym)))) {
1245 ++pos4;
1246 }
1247 if (argsym == sptr) {
1248 pos = i;
1249 seenSym = 1;
1250 } else if (argsym == desc) {
1251 pos2 = i;
1252 seenDesc = 1;
1253 }
1254 if (!pos3 && CCSYMG(argsym) && seenSym) {
1255 pos3 = i;
1256 seenCC = 1;
1257 }
1258 if (CLASSG(argsym)) {
1259 seenClass = 1;
1260 }
1261 }
1262
1263 if (seenCC && seenDesc && seenSym && seenClass) {
1264
1265 NEW(scratch, int, nargs);
1266 assert(scratch, "check_desc: out of memory!", 0, ERR_Fatal);
1267 swap_from = pos2;
1268 swap_to = pos3 + (pos - pos4);
1269 scratch[swap_to] = dpdscp[swap_from];
1270 for (j = i = 0; i < nargs && j < nargs;) {
1271 if (j == swap_to) {
1272 ++j;
1273 continue;
1274 }
1275 if (i == swap_from) {
1276 ++i;
1277 continue;
1278 }
1279 scratch[j] = dpdscp[i];
1280 ++j;
1281 ++i;
1282 }
1283
1284 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
1285 dpdscp[i] = scratch[i];
1286 }
1287 FREE(scratch);
1288 rslt = 1;
1289 }
1290 return rslt;
1291}
1292
1293static void
1294check_desc_args(int func)
1295{
1296 /* Reorder arguments if we're mixing traditional descriptor arguments w/
1297 * type descriptor arguments since they get emitted at different times
1298 * in the front end.
1299 */
1300 int i, nargs, *dpdscp, argsym, swap;
1301 dpdscp = (int *)(aux.dpdsc_base + DPDSCG(func));
1302 nargs = PARAMCTG(func);
1303
1304 swap = 0;
1305 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
1306 argsym = dpdscp[i];
1307 if (0 && CCSYMG(argsym))
1308 break;
1309 if (SDSCG(argsym)) {
1310 DESCARRAYP(SDSCG(argsym), 1); /* needed by type bound procedures */
1311 if (STYPEG(argsym) == ST_PROC) {
1312 /* needed when we have procedure dummy arguments with character
1313 * arguments
1314 */
1315 IS_PROC_DESCRP(SDSCG(argsym), 1);
1316 }
1317
1318 if (check_desc(func, argsym))
1319 swap = 1;
1320 }
1321 }
1322}
1323
1324bool
1325func_has_char_args(SPTR func)
1326{
1327 int i, nargs, *dpdscp;
1328 DTYPE argdtype;
1329
1330 dpdscp = (int *)(aux.dpdsc_base + DPDSCG(func));
1331 nargs = PARAMCTG(func);
1332
1333 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
1334 const SPTR argsym = convertSPTR(dpdscp[i]);
1335 argdtype = DTYPEG(argsym);
1336 if (DTYG(argdtype) == TY_CHAR || DTYG(argdtype) == TY_NCHAR)
1337 return true;
1338 }
1339
1340 return false;
1341}
1342
1343INLINE static int
1344check_struct(DTYPE dtype)
1345{
1346 if (ll_check_struct_return(dtype))
1347 return CLASS_INT4; /* something not CLASS_MEM */
1348 return CLASS_MEM;
1349}
1350
1351static int
1352check_return(DTYPE retdtype)
1353{
1354 if (DTY(retdtype) == TY_STRUCT || DTY(retdtype) == TY_UNION ||
1355 DT_ISCMPLX(retdtype))
1356 return check_struct(retdtype);
1357 if (retdtype == DT_INT8) /* could be the fval of a C_PTR function */
1358 return CLASS_INT8;
1359 return CLASS_INT4; /* something not CLASS_MEM */
1360}
1361
1362INLINE static void
1363align_struct_tmp(int sptr)
1364{
1365#if defined(X86_64)
1366 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_STRUCT && PDALNG(sptr) == 4) {
1367 return;
1368 }
1369#endif
1370
1371 switch (alignment(DTYPEG(sptr))) {
1372 case 0:
1373 case 1:
1374 case 3:
1375 PDALNP(sptr, 2);
1376 break;
1377 case 7:
1378 PDALNP(sptr, 3);
1379 break;
1380 case 15:
1381 PDALNP(sptr, 4);
1382 break;
1383 case 31:
1384 PDALNP(sptr, 5);
1385 break;
1386 default:
1387#if DEBUG
1388 interr("align_struct_tmp: unexpected alignment", alignment(DTYPEG(sptr)),
1389 ERR_Severe);
1390#endif
1391 break;
1392 }
1393}

1395/**
1396 \brief Does the bind(c) function return the struct in register(s)?
1397 \param func_sym the function's symbol
1398 */
1399bool
1400bindC_function_return_struct_in_registers(int func_sym)
1401{
1402 DEBUG_ASSERT(CFUNCG(func_sym), "function not bind(c)");
1403 return check_return(DTYPEG(func_sym)) != CLASS_MEM;
1404}
1405
1406static void
1407handle_bindC_func_ret(int func, finfo_t *pf)
1408{
1409 int retdesc;
1410 int retsym = pf->fval;
1411 const DTYPE retdtype = DTYPEG(retsym);
1412
1413 ADDRTKNP(retsym, 1);
1414 retdesc = check_return(retdtype);
1415 if (retdesc == CLASS_MEM) {
1416 /* Large struct: the address is passed in as an argument */
1417 SCP(retsym, SC_DUMMY);
1418 return;
1419 }
1420 align_struct_tmp(retsym);
1421 pf->ret_sm_struct = retdesc;
1422 pf->ret_align = alignment(retdtype);
1423}

1425static bool
1426process_end_of_list(SPTR func, SPTR osym, int *nlens, DTYPE argdtype)
1427{
1428 if ((needlen(osym, func) &&
1429 (DTYG(argdtype) == TY_CHAR || DTYG(argdtype) == TY_NCHAR)) ||
1430 (IS_PROC_DESCRG(osym) && !HAS_OPT_ARGSG(func) &&
1431 func_has_char_args(func))) {
1432 parg[*nlens] = osym;
1433 *nlens += 1;
1434 return true;
1435 }
1436
1437 return false;
1438}
1439
1440/*
1441 * WARNING: there are nomixedstrlen and mixedstrlen functions to preprocess
1442 * parameters.
1443 */
1444static void
1445pp_params(SPTR func)
1446{
1447 SPTR argsym;
1448 int asym;
1449 DTYPE argdtype;
1450 int nargs;
1451 int *dpdscp;
1452 int nlens;
1453 int byvalue;
1454 finfo_t *pf;
1455
1456 check_desc_args(func);
1457
1458 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1459 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "---pp_params: %s ---\n", SYMNAME(func));
1460 pf = &pfinfo[MIDNUMG(func)]; /* pfinfo alloc'd and init'd by pp_entries */
1461 argdtype = DTYPEG(func);
1462 dpdscp = (int *)(aux.dpdsc_base + DPDSCG(func));
1463 nargs = PARAMCTG(func);
1464 nlens = 0;
1465 byvalue = 0;
1466 pf->mem_off = 8; /* offset for 1st dummy arg */
1467 if (gbl.rutype != RU_FUNC)
1468 goto scan_args;
1469
1470 if (CFUNCG(func) || (CMPLXFUNC_C && DT_ISCMPLX(argdtype))) {
1471 handle_bindC_func_ret(func, &pfinfo[pf->retgrp]);
1472 }
1473
1474 switch (DTY(argdtype)) {
1475 case TY_CHAR:
1476 case TY_NCHAR:
1477 /*
1478 * If this is a function which returns character, the first
1479 * two arguments are for the return length. The last entry in
1480 * the function's dpdsc auxiliary area is the "return" symbol.
1481 */
1482 argsym = convertSPTR(dpdscp[nargs - 1]);
1483 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1484 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "func returns char, through %s\n", SYMNAME(argsym));
1485 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1486 ADDRESSP(argsym, 8);
1487 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1488 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(argsym)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
1489 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1490 argsym = CLENG(argsym);
1491 if (argsym) {
1492 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1493 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "func return len in %s\n", SYMNAME(argsym));
1494 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1495 ADDRESSP(argsym, 12);
1496 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1497 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(argsym)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
1498 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1499 }
1500 pf->mem_off = 16; /* offset for 1st dummy arg */
1501 nargs--;
1502 break;
1503 case TY_CMPLX:
1504 case TY_DCMPLX:
1505 case TY_QCMPLX:
1506 /*
1507 * If this is a function which returns complex, the first arg is
1508 * also for the return value. The last entry in the function's
1509 * dpdsc auxiliary area is the "return" symbol.
1510 */
1511 if (!CFUNCG(func) && !CMPLXFUNC_C) {
1512 argsym = convertSPTR(dpdscp[nargs - 1]);
1513 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1514 ADDRESSP(argsym, 8);
1515 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1516 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(argsym)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
1517 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1518 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1519 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "func also returns complex, through %s\n",
1520 SYMNAME(argsym));
1521 pf->mem_off = 12; /* offset for 1st dummy arg */
1522 nargs--;
1523 }
1524 break;
1525 default:
1526 break;
1527 }
1528scan_args:
1529 /*
1530 * scan through all of the arguments of the function to compute
1531 * how (register or memory area) and where (reg # or offset) the
1532 * arguments area passed. Also, generate the the ili if the argument
1533 * must be copied. If a register argument is not copied, it is recorded
1534 * in the entry's finfo table; if the arg has been copied, a register
1535 * is still "assigned" but it is not recorded (slot is zero).
1536 *
1537 * The only concern for now is arguments which are addresses; the
1538 * exception is the lengths of character args (actually only those
1539 * which are passed length). If compiler is enhanced to allow value
1540 * parameters, presumably there will be some way to distinguish these
1541 * from reference arguments (i.e., a symbol table flag).
1542 */
1543 while (nargs--) {
1544 SPTR osym;
1545 argsym = convertSPTR(*dpdscp++);
1546 osym = argsym;
1547 argdtype = DTYPEG(osym);
1548 if (IS_PROC_DESCRG(osym) && !HAS_OPT_ARGSG(func) &&
1549 process_end_of_list(func, osym, &nlens, argdtype)) {
1550 continue;
1551 }
1552 if (((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) == TY_STRUCT) ||
1553 ((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) == TY_ARRAY) ||
1554 ((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) == TY_UNION))
1555 /* no passbyvalue arrays, structs */
1556 byvalue = 0;
1557 else
1558 byvalue = BYVALDEFAULT(func);
1559
1560 if (PASSBYVALG(argsym))
1561 byvalue = 1;
1562 if (PASSBYREFG(argsym))
1563 byvalue = 0;
1564 if (SCG(argsym) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(argsym) && XBIT(57, 0x80000) &&
1565 SCG(MIDNUMG(argsym)) == SC_DUMMY) {
1566 /* for char, we put pointee in argument list so as to get
1567 * the char length here, but we really pass the pointer
1568 * use the actual pointer */
1569 argsym = MIDNUMG(argsym);
1570 }
1571 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1572 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s in mem area at %d\n", SYMNAME(argsym),
1573 pf->mem_off);
1574 if (COPYPRMSG(argsym))
1575 cp_memarg(argsym, pf->mem_off, DT_ADDR);
1576 else if (DTY(argdtype) == TY_STRUCT) {
1577 REFP(MIDNUMG(argsym), 1);
1578 cp_memarg(argsym, pf->mem_off, DT_ADDR);
1579 } else {
1580 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1581 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1582 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1583 }
1584 if (byvalue) {
1585 if (argdtype == DT_DBLE || argdtype == DT_INT8 || argdtype == DT_LOG8 ||
1586 argdtype == DT_CMPLX)
1587 pf->mem_off += 8;
1588 else if (argdtype == DT_DCMPLX || argdtype == DT_QUAD)
1589 pf->mem_off += 16;
1590 else if (DTY(argdtype) == TY_STRUCT || argdtype == DT_QCMPLX)
1591 pf->mem_off += size_of(argdtype);
1592 else
1593 pf->mem_off += 4;
1594 if (DTY(DTYPEG(argsym)) == TY_STRUCT) {
1595 int src_addr, n;
1596 int src_nme;
1597 int dest_addr;
1598 int dest_nme;
1599 SPTR newsptr = get_byval_local(argsym);
1600 dest_addr = ad_acon(newsptr, 0);
1601 dest_nme = addnme(NT_VAR, newsptr, 0, 0);
1602 src_addr = ad_acon(argsym, 0);
1603 src_nme = NME_VOL;
1604 n = size_of(DTYPEG(newsptr));
1605 chk_block(ad5ili(IL_SMOVEJ, src_addr, dest_addr, src_nme, dest_nme,
1606 n));
1607 }
1608 } else {
1609 pf->mem_off += 4;
1610 }
1611 process_end_of_list(func, osym, &nlens, argdtype);
1612
1613 if ((!HOMEDG(argsym) && (SCG(argsym) == SC_DUMMY)) &&
1614 (!PASSBYREFG(argsym)) &&
1615 (PASSBYVALG(argsym) ||
1616 (BYVALDEFAULT(func) && (((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) != TY_ARRAY) &&
1617 ((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) != TY_STRUCT) &&
1618 ((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) != TY_UNION))))) {
1619 if (!gbl.outlined && !ISTASKDUPG(GBL_CURRFUNC))
1620 cp_byval_mem_arg(argsym);
1621 PASSBYVALP(argsym, 1);
1622 }
1623 }
1624 /*
1625 * go through the list of character arguments. Here we only care
1626 * about processing those which have passed length; we still need
1627 * to keep track of the registers and the offset into the memory
1628 * argument area for those char arguments which are declared with
1629 * constant lengths.
1630 */
1631 dpdscp = parg;
1632 while (nlens--) {
1633 argsym = convertSPTR(*dpdscp);
1634 if (SCG(argsym) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(argsym) && XBIT(57, 0x80000) &&
1635 SCG(MIDNUMG(argsym)) == SC_DUMMY) {
1636 /* for char, we put pointee in argument list so as to get
1637 * the char length here, but we really pass the pointer
1638 * use the actual pointer */
1639 *dpdscp = MIDNUMG(argsym);
1640 }
1641 dpdscp++;
1642 argdtype = DTYPEG(argsym);
1643 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1644 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s.len in mem area at %d\n", SYMNAME(argsym),
1645 pf->mem_off);
1646 if (
1647 (!HAS_OPT_ARGSG(func) && IS_PROC_DESCRG(argsym)) ||
1648 (
1649 !AUTOBJG(argsym) &&
1650 (argsym = CLENG(argsym)))) {
1651 if (COPYPRMSG(argsym))
1652 cp_memarg(argsym, pf->mem_off, expb.charlen_dtype);
1653 else {
1654 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1655 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1656 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1657 }
1658 }
1659 pf->mem_off += 4;
1660 }
1661}
1662
1663/*
1664 * WARNING: there are nomixedstrlen and mixedstrlen functions to preprocess
1665 * parameters.
1666 */
1667static void
1668pp_params_mixedstrlen(int func)
1669{
1670 SPTR argsym;
1671 int asym;
1672 DTYPE argdtype;
1673 int nargs;
1674 int *dpdscp;
1675 int nlens;
1676 int byvalue;
1677 finfo_t *pf;
1678
1679 check_desc_args(func);
1680
1681 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1682 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "---pp_params_mixedstrlen: %s ---\n", SYMNAME(func));
1683 pf = &pfinfo[MIDNUMG(func)]; /* pfinfo alloc'd and init'd by pp_entries */
1684 argdtype = DTYPEG(func);
1685 dpdscp = (int *)(aux.dpdsc_base + DPDSCG(func));
1686 nargs = PARAMCTG(func);
1687 nlens = 0;
1688 byvalue = 0;
1689
1690 pf->mem_off = 8; /* offset for 1st dummy arg */
1691 if (gbl.rutype != RU_FUNC)
1692 goto scan_args;
1693 switch (DTY(argdtype)) {
1694 case TY_CHAR:
1695 case TY_NCHAR:
1696 /*
1697 * If this is a function which returns character, the first
1698 * two arguments are for the return length. The last entry in
1699 * the function's dpdsc auxiliary area is the "return" symbol.
1700 */
1701 argsym = convertSPTR(dpdscp[nargs - 1]);
1702 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1703 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "func returns char, through %s\n", SYMNAME(argsym));
1704 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1705 ADDRESSP(argsym, 8);
1706 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1707 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(argsym)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
1708 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1709 argsym = CLENG(argsym);
1710 if (argsym) {
1711 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1712 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "func return len in %s\n", SYMNAME(argsym));
1713 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1714 ADDRESSP(argsym, 12);
1715 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1716 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(argsym)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
1717 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1718 }
1719 pf->mem_off = 16; /* offset for 1st dummy arg */
1720 nargs--;
1721 break;
1722 case TY_CMPLX:
1723 case TY_DCMPLX:
1724 /*
1725 * If this is a function which returns complex, the first arg is
1726 * also for the return value. The last entry in the function's
1727 * dpdsc auxiliary area is the "return" symbol.
1728 */
1729 argsym = convertSPTR(dpdscp[nargs - 1]);
1730 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1731 ADDRESSP(argsym, 8);
1732 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1733 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(argsym)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
1734 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1735 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1736 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "func also returns complex, through %s\n",
1737 SYMNAME(argsym));
1738 pf->mem_off = 12; /* offset for 1st dummy arg */
1739 nargs--;
1740 break;
1741 default:
1742 break;
1743 }
1744scan_args:
1745 /*
1746 * scan through all of the arguments of the function to compute
1747 * how (register or memory area) and where (reg # or offset) the
1748 * arguments area passed. Also, generate the the ili if the argument
1749 * must be copied. If a register argument is not copied, it is recorded
1750 * in the entry's finfo table; if the arg has been copied, a register
1751 * is still "assigned" but it is not recorded (slot is zero).
1752 *
1753 * The only concern for now is arguments which are addresses; the
1754 * exception is the lengths of character args (actually only those
1755 * which are passed length). If compiler is enhanced to allow value
1756 * parameters, presumably there will be some way to distinguish these
1757 * from reference arguments (i.e., a symbol table flag).
1758 */
1759 while (nargs--) {
1760 int osym;
1761 argsym = convertSPTR(*dpdscp++);
1762 osym = argsym;
1763 if (((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) == TY_STRUCT) ||
1764 ((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) == TY_ARRAY) ||
1765 ((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) == TY_UNION))
1766 /* no passbyvalue arrays, structs */
1767 byvalue = 0;
1768 else
1769 byvalue = BYVALDEFAULT(func);
1770
1771 if (PASSBYVALG(argsym))
1772 byvalue = 1;
1773 if (PASSBYREFG(argsym))
1774 byvalue = 0;
1775 if (SCG(argsym) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(argsym) && XBIT(57, 0x80000) &&
1776 SCG(MIDNUMG(argsym)) == SC_DUMMY) {
1777 /* char pointers, we put the pointee on the argument
1778 * list so as to get the char length, but we really pass
1779 * the pointer.
1780 * replace by the actual pointer */
1781 argsym = MIDNUMG(argsym);
1782 }
1783 argdtype = DTYPEG(osym);
1784 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1785 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s in mem area at %d\n", SYMNAME(argsym),
1786 pf->mem_off);
1787 if (COPYPRMSG(argsym)) {
1788 cp_memarg(argsym, pf->mem_off, DT_ADDR);
1789 } else if (DTY(argdtype) == TY_STRUCT) {
1790 REFP(MIDNUMG(argsym), 1);
1791 cp_memarg(argsym, pf->mem_off, DT_ADDR);
1792 } else {
1793 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1794 ADDRESSP(argsym, pf->mem_off);
1795 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1796 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(argsym)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
1797 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1798 }
1799 if (byvalue) {
1800 if (argdtype == DT_DBLE || argdtype == DT_INT8 || argdtype == DT_LOG8 ||
1801 argdtype == DT_CMPLX)
1802 pf->mem_off += 8;
1803 else if (argdtype == DT_DCMPLX || argdtype == DT_QUAD)
1804 pf->mem_off += 16;
1805 else if (DTY(argdtype) == TY_STRUCT || argdtype == DT_QCMPLX)
1806 pf->mem_off += size_of(argdtype);
1807 else
1808 pf->mem_off += 4;
1809 } else {
1810 pf->mem_off += 4;
1811 }
1812
1813 /*
1814 * character length.
1815 */
1816 if ((DTYG(argdtype) == TY_CHAR || DTYG(argdtype) == TY_NCHAR) &&
1817 needlen(argsym, func)) {
1818 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
1819 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%s.len in mem area at %d\n", SYMNAME(argsym),
1820 pf->mem_off);
1821 if (
1822 !AUTOBJG(argsym) &&
1823 (argsym = CLENG(osym))) {
1824 if (COPYPRMSG(argsym))
1825 cp_memarg(argsym, pf->mem_off, expb.charlen_dtype);
1826 else {
1827 MEMARGP(argsym, 1);
1828 ADDRESSP(argsym, pf->mem_off);
1829 asym = mk_argasym(argsym);
1830 ADDRESSP(asym, ADDRESSG(argsym)); /* propagate ADDRESS */
1831 MEMARGP(asym, 1);
1832 }
1833 }
1834 pf->mem_off += 4;
1835 }
1836 if ((!HOMEDG(argsym) && (SCG(argsym) == SC_DUMMY)) &&
1837 (!PASSBYREFG(argsym)) &&
1838 (PASSBYVALG(argsym) ||
1839 (BYVALDEFAULT(func) && ((DTY(DTYPEG(argsym))) != TY_ARRAY)))) {
1840 cp_byval_mem_arg(argsym);
1841 PASSBYVALP(argsym, 1);
1842 }
1843
1844 } /* end while */
1845}

1847#ifdef FLANG2_EXPRTE_UNUSED
1848static int
1849get_frame_off(INT off)
1850{
1851 int ili;
1852
1853 /* Compute the address of the memory argument by relying on
1854 * a dummy symbol whose address is the first memory argument
1855 * immediately upon entry, i.e., after the return address has been pushed
1856 * on the stack by the call instruction but before any manipulation
1857 * of %rbp by the cg.
1858 * The actual address computation will consist of an ACON whose
1859 * symbol is the dummy symbol and whose offset is relative to
1860 * the dummy symbol.
1861 */
1862 if (memarg_var == 0) {
1863 memarg_var = getccsym('Q', expb.gentmps++, ST_VAR);
1864 SCP(memarg_var, SC_DUMMY);
1865 DTYPEP(memarg_var, DT_CPTR);
1866 REDUCP(memarg_var, 1); /* mark sym --> no further indirection */
1867 HOMEDP(memarg_var, 0);
1868 ADDRTKNP(memarg_var, 1);
1869 }
1870 ili = ad_acon(memarg_var, off - MEMARG_OFFSET);
1871 return ili;
1872}
1873#endif

1875/* from exp_c.c */
1876static void
1877ldst_size(DTYPE dtype, ILI_OP *ldo, ILI_OP *sto, int *siz)
1878{
1879 *ldo = IL_LD;
1880 *sto = IL_ST;
1881
1882 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
1883 case TY_BINT:
1884 case TY_CHAR:
1885 *siz = MSZ_SBYTE;
1886 break;
1887 case TY_SINT:
1888 case TY_SLOG:
1889 case TY_NCHAR:
1890 *siz = MSZ_SHWORD;
1891 break;
1892 case TY_FLOAT:
1893 case TY_CMPLX:
1894 *siz = MSZ_F4;
1895 *ldo = IL_LDSP;
1896 *sto = IL_STSP;
1897 break;
1898 case TY_INT8:
1899 *siz = MSZ_I8;
1900 *ldo = IL_LDKR;
1901 *sto = IL_STKR;
1902 break;
1903 case TY_DBLE:
1904 case TY_DCMPLX:
1905 *siz = MSZ_F8;
1906 *ldo = IL_LDDP;
1907 *sto = IL_STDP;
1908 break;
1909#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
1910 case TY_QUAD:
1911 case TY_QCMPLX:
1912 *siz = MSZ_F16;
1913 *ldo = IL_LDQP;
1914 *sto = IL_STQP;
1915 break;
1916#endif
1917 case TY_PTR:
1918 *siz = MSZ_WORD;
1919 *ldo = IL_LDA;
1920 *sto = IL_STA;
1921 break;
1922 case TY_STRUCT:
1923 switch (DTyAlgTySize(dtype)) {
1924 case 1:
1925 *siz = MSZ_BYTE;
1926 break;
1927 case 2:
1928 *siz = MSZ_SHWORD;
1929 break;
1930 case 8:
1931 *siz = MSZ_F8;
1932 break;
1933 case 16:
1934 *siz = MSZ_F16;
1935 break;
1936 case 4:
1937 default:
1938 *siz = MSZ_WORD;
1939 }
1940 break;
1941 case TY_BLOG:
1942 *siz = MSZ_SBYTE;
1943 break;
1944 case TY_INT:
1945 default:
1946 *siz = MSZ_WORD;
1947 }
1948 switch (*siz) {
1949 case MSZ_FWORD:
1950 *ldo = IL_LDSP;
1951 *sto = IL_STSP;
1952 break;
1953 case MSZ_DFLWORD:
1954 *ldo = IL_LDDP;
1955 *sto = IL_STDP;
1956 break;
1957 }
1958} /* ldst_size */

1960/***************************************************************/
1961/* F o r t r a n S t r i n g S u p p o r t */
1962/***************************************************************/
1963
1964/* for the character*1 load/store optimization, need a names entry
1965 * for use in the load/store ili which is sufficient for cg to
1966 * correctly schedule the loads/stores when loads/stores of overlaid
1967 * data (MAPs, see tpr 564) are present. NME_UNK is insufficient
1968 * since cg does not always consider NME_UNK to conflict with all
1969 * others. The macro NME_STR1 is used when the optimization occurs;
1970 * it's defined to be the actual nme which is used. 'Precise' nmes
1971 * aren't used since the optimization phases do not expect to see
1972 * Fortran character variables.
1973 */
1974#define NME_STR1 NME_VOL
1975
1976/* copy an argument passed by value to it's identically named
1977 compiler created SC_LOCAL
1978 this is used only for args not passed in registers
1979*/
1980static void
1981cp_byval_mem_arg(SPTR argsptr)
1982{
1983 SPTR newsptr;
1984 ILI_OP ldo, sto;
1985 int ms_siz;
1986 int ilix;
1987 int val, val_nme;
1988 int addr, addr_nme;
1989 DTYPE dtype = DTYPEG(argsptr);
1990
1991 ldst_size(dtype, &ldo, &sto, &ms_siz);
1992 newsptr = get_byval_local(argsptr);
1993 HOMEDP(argsptr, 1);
1994 MEMARGP(argsptr, 0);
1995
1996 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_STRUCT) {
1997 if (dtype != DT_CMPLX && dtype != DT_DCMPLX) {
1998 val = ad_acon(argsptr, 0);
1999 val_nme = addnme(NT_VAR, argsptr, 0, 0);
2000 ilix = ad3ili(ldo, val, val_nme, ms_siz);
2001 addr = ad_acon(newsptr, 0);
2002 if (dtype == DT_CHAR || dtype == DT_NCHAR) {
2003 addr_nme = NME_STR1;
2004 } else {
2005 addr_nme = addnme(NT_VAR, newsptr, 0, 0);
2006 }
2007 ilix = ad4ili(sto, ilix, addr, addr_nme, ms_siz);
2008 chk_block(ilix);
2009 } else {
2010 int val_nme2, addr_nme2, sz;
2011 sz = size_of(dtype);
2012 /* copy the real part */
2013 val = ad_acon(argsptr, 0);
2014 val_nme = addnme(NT_VAR, argsptr, 0, 0);
2015 val_nme2 = addnme(NT_MEM, SPTR_NULL, val_nme, 0);
2016 ilix = ad3ili(ldo, val, val_nme2, ms_siz);
2017 addr = ad_acon(newsptr, 0);
2018 addr_nme = addnme(NT_VAR, newsptr, 0, 0);
2019 addr_nme2 = addnme(NT_MEM, SPTR_NULL, addr_nme, 0);
2020 ilix = ad4ili(sto, ilix, addr, addr_nme2, ms_siz);
2021 chk_block(ilix);
2022 val = ad_acon(argsptr, sz / 2);
2023 val_nme2 = addnme(NT_MEM, NOSYM, val_nme, sz / 2);
2024 ilix = ad3ili(ldo, val, val_nme2, ms_siz);
2025 addr = ad_acon(newsptr, sz / 2);
2026 addr_nme2 = addnme(NT_MEM, NOSYM, addr_nme, sz / 2);
2027 ilix = ad4ili(sto, ilix, addr, addr_nme2, ms_siz);
2028 chk_block(ilix);
2029 }
2030 }
2031 if (gbl.internal == 1) {
2032 sym_is_refd(argsptr);
2033 HOMEDP(argsptr, 0);
2034 }
2035}

2071/***************************************************************/
2072
2073int
2074exp_alloca(ILM *ilmp)
2075{
2076 int op1, op2;
2077
2078 alloca_flag = 1;
2079 op1 = ILI_OF(ILM_OPND(ilmp, 1)); /* nelems */
2080 op2 = ILI_OF(ILM_OPND(ilmp, 2)); /* nbytes */
2081 /** sptr = ILM_OPND(ilmp, 3); sym and currently ignored **/
2082 /** tmp = ILM_OPND(ilmp, 4); stc and currently ignored **/
2083 /*
2084 * final size must be a multiple of 16:
2085 * (nelems*nbytes + 15) & ~0xfL
2086 */
2087 op2 = ikmove(op2);
2088 op1 = ad2ili(IL_KMUL, op1, op2);
2089 if (!XBIT(54, 0x10)) {
2090 /** runtime adjusts the size **/
2091 (void)mk_prototype("__builtin_aa", "pure", DT_ADDR, 1, DT_INT8);
2092 } else {
2093 op1 = ad2ili(IL_KADD, op1, ad_kconi(15));
2094 op1 = ad2ili(IL_KAND, op1, ad_kcon(0xffffffff, 0xfffffff0));
2095 }
2096 op2 = ad1ili(IL_NULL, 0);
2097 op2 = ad2ili(IL_ARGKR, op1, op2);
2098 if (!XBIT(54, 0x10))
2099 op1 = ad2ili(IL_JSR, mkfunc("__builtin_aa"), op2);
2100 else
2101 op1 = ad2ili(IL_JSR, mkfunc("__builtin_alloca"), op2);
2102 return ad2ili(IL_DFRAR, op1, AR_RETVAL);
2103}

2106
2107static void gen_funcret(finfo_t *);
2108
2109void
2110exp_end(ILM *ilmp, int curilm, bool is_func)
2111{
2112 int tmp;
2113 int func;
2114 int sym;
2115 finfo_t *pf;
2116 int exit_bih;
2117
2118 if (expb.retlbl != 0) {
2119 exp_label(expb.retlbl);
2120 expb.retlbl = SPTR_NULL;
2121 }
2122 if (allocharhdr) {
2123 /* if character temps were allocated, need to free the
2124 * list of allocated areas created by the run-time.
2125 */
2126 int ld;
2127
2128 /* ftn_str_free(allocharhdr) */
2129 ld = ad_acon(allocharhdr, 0);
2130 ld = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ld, addnme(NT_VAR, allocharhdr, 0, 0));
2131 sym = frte_func(mkfunc, mkRteRtnNm(RTE_str_free));
2132 tmp = ad1ili(IL_NULL, 0);
2133 tmp = ad3ili(IL_ARGAR, ld, tmp, 0);
2134 tmp = ad2ili(IL_JSR, sym, tmp);
2135 iltb.callfg = 1;
2136 chk_block(tmp);
2137 }
2138
2139 exp_restore_mxcsr();
2140
2141 if (is_func) {
2142 SPTR exit_lab;
2143 SPTR next_lab;
2144 int load_retgrp;
2145 int currgrp;
2146
2147 if (retgrp_cnt > 1) {
2148 load_retgrp = ad3ili(IL_LD, ad_acon(retgrp_var, 0),
2149 addnme(NT_VAR, retgrp_var, 0, 0), MSZ_WORD);
2150 exit_lab = getlab();
2151 } else {
2152 exit_lab = SPTR_NULL;
2153 }
2154 /*
2155 * generate test, move, branch for all but the first return
2156 * group.
2157 */
2158 for (currgrp = 1; currgrp < retgrp_cnt; currgrp++) {
2159 /* generate code sequence for a group as follows:
2160 * if (load_retgrp != currgrp) got to next_lab;
2161 * result <--- load currgrp's fval;
2162 * goto exit_lab;
2163 * next_lab:
2164 */
2165 next_lab = getlab();
2166 RFCNTI(next_lab);
2167 tmp = ad4ili(IL_ICJMP, load_retgrp, ad_icon(currgrp), 2, next_lab);
2168 chk_block(tmp);
2169 gen_funcret(&pfinfo[currgrp]);
2170 RFCNTI(exit_lab);
2171 tmp = ad1ili(IL_JMP, exit_lab);
2172 chk_block(tmp);
2173 exp_label(next_lab);
2174 }
2175 /* generate move for last block */
2176 gen_funcret(&pfinfo[0]);
2177 if (exit_lab)
2178 exp_label(exit_lab);
2179 }
2180 if (gbl.arets) {
2181 int addr;
2182 int nme;
2183 int move;
2184
2185 addr = ad_acon(expb.aret_tmp, 0);
2186 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, expb.aret_tmp, 0, 0);
2187 tmp = ad3ili(IL_LD, addr, nme, MSZ_WORD);
2188 move = ad2ili(IL_MVIR, tmp, IR_ARET);
2189 chk_block(move);
2190 }
2191 if (flg.opt >= 1 && expb.curilt != 0) {
2192 flsh_block(); /* at the higher opt levels, the exit */
2193 cr_block(); /* block is a stand-alone block */
2194 }
2195 /* xon/xoff stuff goes here */
2196
2197 /* exit debug stuff goes here */
2198
2199 tmp = ad1ili(IL_EXIT, gbl.currsub);
2200 expb.curilt = addilt(expb.curilt, tmp);
2201 BIH_XT(expb.curbih) = 1;
2202 BIH_LAST(expb.curbih) = 1;
2203 exit_bih = expb.curbih;
2204 wr_block();
2205 BIH_EX(gbl.entbih) = expb.flags.bits.callfg;
2206 BIH_SMOVE(gbl.entbih) = smove_flag;
2207 aux.curr_entry->flags = 0;
2208 if (mscall_flag)
2209 aux.curr_entry->flags |= 0x40000000;
2210 if (alloca_flag)
2211 aux.curr_entry->flags |= 0x80000000;
2212 /*
2213 * scan through all the entries to store return group value if necessary.
2214 */
2215 if (gbl.rutype == RU_PROG)
2216 goto exp_end_ret;
2217 for (func = gbl.entries; func != NOSYM; func = SYMLKG(func)) {
2218 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
2219 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "---exp_end: %s ---\n", SYMNAME(func));
2220 expb.curbih = BIHNUMG(func);
2221 BIH_EX(expb.curbih) = expb.flags.bits.callfg; /* ALL entry bihs */
2222 BIH_SMOVE(expb.curbih) = smove_flag;
2223 if (retgrp_cnt > 1) {
2224 pf = &pfinfo[MIDNUMG(func)];
2225 rdilts(expb.curbih); /* get entry block */
2226 expb.curilt = ILT_PREV(0);
2227 tmp = ad_icon(pf->retgrp);
2228 tmp = ad4ili(IL_ST, tmp, ad_acon(retgrp_var, 0),
2229 addnme(NT_VAR, retgrp_var, 0, 0), MSZ_WORD);
2230 chk_block(tmp);
2231 wrilts(expb.curbih);
2232 }
2233 }
2234 /*
2235 * For multiple entries using the WINNT calling convention, must store
2236 * the number of bytes passed to each entry in a temporary. This store
2237 * must appear in the prologue of each entry -- the code generator will
2238 * load the temporary and use its value to pop the arguments from the
2239 * stack. A sufficient test for generating the store is if the temporary
2240 * was created (saved in aux.curr_entry->ent_save),
2241 */
2242 if (aux.curr_entry->ent_save) {
2243 int addr, nme;
2244 addr = ad_acon(aux.curr_entry->ent_save, 0);
2245 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, aux.curr_entry->ent_save, 0, 0);
2246 for (func = gbl.entries; func != NOSYM; func = SYMLKG(func)) {
2247 expb.curbih = BIHNUMG(func);
2248 rdilts(expb.curbih); /* get entry block */
2249 expb.curilt = ILT_PREV(0);
2250 if (ARGSIZEG(func) < 0)
2251 tmp = ad_icon(0);
2252 else
2253 tmp = ad_icon(ARGSIZEG(func));
2254 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
2255 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "---storing %d in %s ---\n",
2256 CONVAL2G(ILI_OPND(tmp, 1)), SYMNAME(aux.curr_entry->ent_save));
2257 tmp = ad4ili(IL_ST, tmp, addr, nme, MSZ_WORD);
2258 chk_block(tmp);
2259 wrilts(expb.curbih);
2260 }
2261 }
2262
2263 freearea(1); /* duumy arg processing (alloc'd in pp_entries) */
2264
2265exp_end_ret:
2266 if (allocharhdr) {
2267 /* if character temps were allocated, need to initialize the
2268 * head of a list of allocated areas created by the run-time.
2269 */
2270 int st;
2271
2272 tmp = ad_acon(SPTR_NULL, 0);
2273 st = ad_acon(allocharhdr, 0);
2274 st = ad3ili(IL_STA, tmp, st, addnme(NT_VAR, allocharhdr, 0, 0));
2275 for (func = gbl.entries; func != NOSYM; func = SYMLKG(func)) {
2276 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
2277 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "---init allocharhdr: %s in %s---\n",
2278 SYMNAME(allocharhdr), SYMNAME(func));
2279 expb.curbih = BIH_NEXT(BIHNUMG(func));
2280 rdilts(expb.curbih); /* get block after entry block */
2281 expb.curilt = 0;
2282 /* allocharhdr = NULL; */
2283 chk_block(st);
2284 wrilts(expb.curbih);
2285 }
2286 }
2287
2288 /* emit any mp initialization for the function & its entries */
2289 exp_mp_func_prologue(true);
2290
2291 if (!XBIT(121, 0x01) || /* -Mnoframe isn't specified */
2292 (flg.debug && !XBIT(123, 0x400)) || /* -debug is set */
2293 (flg.profile && XBIT(129, 0x800)) || /* -Minstrument */
2294 XBIT(34, 0x200) || /* -Mconcur */
2295 flg.smp || /* -mp */
2296 alloca_flag || /* alloca present */
2297 (gbl.internal /* contains an internal subprogram or is an
2298 * internal subprogram. */
2299 && !gbl.cudaemu) || /* Don't use a frame pointer when emulating
2300 * CUDA device code. */
2301 gbl.vfrets || /* contains variable format expressions */
2302 /* linux main now aligns the stack - so can't allow -Mnoframe */
2303 (XBIT(119, 0x8000000) && gbl.rutype == RU_PROG) ||
2304 /* -Msmartalloc=huge[:n] */
2305 (XBIT(129, 0x10000000) && gbl.rutype == RU_PROG) ||
2306 aux.curr_entry->ent_save > 0 /* is this a fortran routine with
2307 * multiple entries and mscall */
2308 )
2309 aux.curr_entry->flags |= 0x100; /* bit set ==> must use frame pointer */
2310
2311 /* we can't afford a third global register unless -Mnoframe is allowed */
2312 if (aux.curr_entry->flags & 0x100)
2313 mr_reset_numglobals(1); /* must use frame - reduce nglobals by 1 */
2314 else
2315 mr_reset_numglobals(0); /* -Mnoframe ok */
2316
2317 /* only perform floating-point caching at -O2 or higher */
2318 if (flg.opt < 2 || XBIT(8, 0x400) || XBIT(8, 0x1000) || flg.ieee ||
2319 XBIT(6, 0x100) || XBIT(6, 0x200))
2320 mr_reset_frglobals();
2321
2322 if (DOREG1) { /* assign registers for opt level 1 */
2323 expb.curbih = exit_bih;
2324 reg_assign1();
2325 }
2326 /*
2327 * for opt levels 0 and 1, check if this function is a terminal
2328 * routine.
2329 */
2330 if (flg.opt <= 1)
2331 chk_terminal_func(gbl.entbih, expb.curbih);
2332
2333 /* chk_savears(expb.curbih) needed? */
2334
2335 /* final stuff to cleanup at the end of a function */
2336 expb.arglist = 0;
2337 expb.flags.bits.callfg = 0;
2338 mkrtemp_end();
2339}

2341static void
2342gen_bindC_retval(finfo_t *fp)
2343{
2344 const SPTR fval = fp->fval;
2345 const int retv = ad_acon(fval, 0);
2346 const int nme = addnme(NT_VAR, fval, 0, 0);
2347 int ilix = retv;
2348
2349 if (fp->ret_sm_struct) {
2350 ilix = ad2ili(IL_MVAR, retv, RES_IR(0));
2351 ADDRTKNP(fval, 1);
2352 } else {
2353 switch (IL_RES(ILI_OPC(ilix))) {
2354 case ILIA_AR:
2355 ilix = ad2ili(IL_LDA, ilix, nme);
2356 ilix = ad2ili(IL_MVAR, ilix, RES_IR(0));
2357 break;
2358 case ILIA_IR:
2359 ilix = ad2ili(IL_MVIR, ilix, RES_IR(0));
2360 break;
2361 case ILIA_SP:
2362 if (ILI_OPC(ilix) != IL_LDSP && ILI_OPC(ilix) != IL_FCON) {
2363 const SPTR sfval = fp->fval;
2364 ilix = ad4ili(IL_STSP, ilix, ad_acon(sfval, 0),
2365 addnme(NT_VAR, sfval, 0, 0), MSZ_F4);
2366 chk_block(ilix);
2367 ilix = ad3ili(IL_LDSP, ad_acon(sfval, 0),
2368 addnme(NT_VAR, sfval, 0, 0), MSZ_F4);
2369 }
2370 ilix = ad2ili(IL_MVSP, ilix, RES_XR(0));
2371 break;
2372 case ILIA_DP:
2373 if (ILI_OPC(ilix) != IL_LDDP && ILI_OPC(ilix) != IL_DCON) {
2374 const SPTR sfval = fp->fval;
2375 ilix = ad4ili(IL_STDP, ilix, ad_acon(sfval, 0),
2376 addnme(NT_VAR, sfval, 0, 0), MSZ_F8);
2377 chk_block(ilix);
2378 ilix = ad3ili(IL_LDDP, ad_acon(sfval, 0),
2379 addnme(NT_VAR, sfval, 0, 0), MSZ_F8);
2380 }
2381 if (ILI_OPC(ilix) == IL_LD256) {
2382 ilix = ad2ili(IL_MV256, ilix, RES_XR(0)); /*m256*/
2383 } else if (ILI_OPC(ilix) != IL_LDQ) {
2384 ilix = ad2ili(IL_MVDP, ilix, RES_XR(0));
2385 } else {
2386 ilix = ad2ili(IL_MVQ, ilix, RES_XR(0)); /*m128*/
2387 }
2388 break;
2389 case ILIA_KR:
2390 ilix = ad2ili(IL_MVKR, ilix, RES_IR(0));
2391 break;
2392 default:
2393 interr("expand:illegal return expr", retv, ERR_Severe);
2394 break;
2395 }
2396 }
2397 if (EXPDBG(8, 256))
2398 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "gen_retval %d @ %d\n", ilix, gbl.lineno);
2399 /*
2400 * check what is in the current block to see if the block has to be
2401 * written out
2402 */
2403 chk_block(ilix);
2404}
2405
2406static void
2407gen_funcret(finfo_t *fp)
2408{
2409 int addr;
2410 int nme;
2411 int ili1;
2412 int move;
2413 SPTR fval = fp->fval;
2414 int fvaltyp = DTY(DTYPEG(fval));
2415
2416 if (CFUNCG(gbl.currsub) || (CMPLXFUNC_C && TY_ISCMPLX(fvaltyp))) {
2417 gen_bindC_retval(fp);
2418 return;
2419 }
2420 addr = ad_acon(fval, 0);
2421 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, fval, 0, 0);
2422 /*
2423 * if it's possible that fvar has storage SC_DUMMY AND we need
2424 * to generate a load, then we need a LDA:
2425 * if (SCG(fval) == SC_DUMMY)
2426 * addr = ad2ili(IL_LDA, addr, nme);
2427 */
2428 switch (fvaltyp) {
2429 case TY_CHAR:
2430 case TY_NCHAR:
2431 return;
2432 case TY_CMPLX:
2433 case TY_DCMPLX:
2434#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
2435 case TY_QCMPLX:
2436#endif
2437 if (!CFUNCG(gbl.currsub) && !CMPLXFUNC_C)
2438 return;
2439 move = ad2ili(IL_MVAR, addr, RES_IR(0));
2440 ADDRTKNP(fval, 1);
2441 if (XBIT(121, 0x400)) {
2442 int gret;
2443 gret = ad3ili(IL_RETURN, addr, DTYPEG(fval), nme);
2444 ILI_ALT(move) = gret;
2445 }
2446 break;
2447 case TY_REAL:
2448 ili1 = ad3ili(IL_LDSP, addr, nme, MSZ_F4);
2449 move = ad2ili(IL_MVSP, ili1, FR_RETVAL);
2450 break;
2451 case TY_DBLE:
2452 ili1 = ad3ili(IL_LDDP, addr, nme, MSZ_F8);
2453 move = ad2ili(IL_MVDP, ili1, FR_RETVAL);
2454 break;
2455#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
2456 case TY_QUAD:
2457 ili1 = ad3ili(IL_LDQP, addr, nme, MSZ_F16);
2458 move = ad2ili(IL_MVQ, ili1, FR_RETVAL);
2459 break;
2460#endif
2461 case TY_BINT:
2462 case TY_BLOG:
2463 ili1 = ad3ili(IL_LD, addr, nme, MSZ_SBYTE);
2464 move = ad2ili(IL_MVIR, ili1, IR_RETVAL);
2465 break;
2466 case TY_SINT:
2467 case TY_SLOG:
2468 ili1 = ad3ili(IL_LD, addr, nme, MSZ_SHWORD);
2469 move = ad2ili(IL_MVIR, ili1, IR_RETVAL);
2470 break;
2471 case TY_INT:
2472 case TY_LOG:
2473 ili1 = ad3ili(IL_LD, addr, nme, MSZ_WORD);
2474 move = ad2ili(IL_MVIR, ili1, IR_RETVAL);
2475 break;
2476 case TY_INT8:
2477 case TY_LOG8:
2478 ili1 = ad3ili(IL_LDKR, addr, nme, MSZ_I8);
2479 move = ad2ili(IL_MVKR, ili1, KR_RETVAL);
2480 break;
2481 default:
2482 interr("gen_funcret: illegal dtype, sym", fval, ERR_Severe);
2483 return;
2484 }
2485
2486 chk_block(move);
2487}

2490
2491static SWEL *sw_array; /**< linear form of the switch list, incl default */
2492static int sw_temp; /**< acon ili of temp holding value of switch val */
2493static int sw_val; /**< ili of the original switch value; becomes a load
2494 of a temp if it's necessary to temp store value */
2495static void genswitch(INT, INT);
2496
2497/**
2498 \brief expand a computed go to
2499
2500 this processing is similiar to the processing of a switch by pgc. The
2501 exception is that the switch list is already ordered as a table in increasing
2502 order. pgc must first create a table of the switch values.
2503 */
2504void
2505exp_cgoto(ILM *ilmp, int curilm)
2506{
2507 INT i;
2508 INT n; /* # of cases */
2509 INT cval;
2510
2511 sw_val = ILI_OF(ILM_OPND(ilmp, 1));
2512 sw_temp = 0;
2513 i = ILM_OPND(ilmp, 2); /* index from switch_base locating default */
2514 sw_array = switch_base + i;
2515 n = sw_array[0].val;
2516#if DEBUG
2517 if (flg.dbg[10] != 0) {
2518 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil,
2519 "\n\n Switch: %-5d line: %-5d n: %-5d default: %-5d\n", curilm,
2520 gbl.lineno, n, sw_array[0].clabel);
2521 for (i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
2522 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " %10d %5d~\n", sw_array[i].val,
2523 sw_array[i].clabel);
2524 }
2525 }
2526#endif
2527 assert(n != 0, "exp_cgoto: cnt is zero, at ilm", curilm, ERR_Severe);
2528 if (ILI_OPC(sw_val) == IL_ICON) {
2529 /*
2530 * switch value is a constant -- search switch list for the equal
2531 * value and generate a jump to that label. If not found, the jump
2532 * to the default will take place
2533 */
2534 cval = CONVAL2G(ILI_OPND(sw_val, 1));
2535 i = 1; /* first in switch list */
2536 do {
2537 if (cval == sw_array[i].val)
2538 chk_block(ad1ili(IL_JMP, sw_array[i].clabel));
2539 else
2540 RFCNTD(sw_array[i].clabel);
2541 } while (++i <= n);
2542 chk_block(ad1ili(IL_JMP, sw_array[0].clabel));
2543 return;
2544 }
2545 genswitch(1, n);
2546}
2547
2548/**
2549 \param lb lower bound of switch array
2550 \param ub upper bound of switch array
2551 */
2552static void
2553genswitch(INT lb, INT ub)
2554{
2555 UINT ncases;
2556 UINT range;
2557 int i;
2558
2559 ncases = ub - lb + 1;
2560 range = sw_array[ub].val - sw_array[lb].val + 1;
2561#if DEBUG
2562 if (flg.dbg[10])
2563 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "genswitch: lb: %d, ub: %d\n", lb, ub);
2564#endif
2565 if (ncases >= 6 && range <= (3 * ncases)) {
2566 /*
2567 * Use a memory table of addresses for the switch. The JMPM
2568 * ili is created which fetches to branch address from a table
2569 * in memory based on the value of the switch expression.
2570 * This value is normalized to 0 (first entry contains the first
2571 * case label)
2572 */
2573 int ilix;
2574 SWEL *swhdr;
2575 /*
2576 * First, locate beginning of the switch list for this range in
2577 * the original area. Also, terminate the last element in the list.
2578 */
2579 swhdr = &sw_array[lb];
2580 sw_array[ub].next = 0;
2581 ilix = ad_icon(range);
2582 /*
2583 * for TARGET_LLVM, pairs of case values and labels are present to
2584 * the llvm switch instruction, we should not be normalizing the
2585 * switch expression to zero.
2586 */
2587 ilix = ad4ili(IL_JMPM, sw_val, ilix,
2588 mk_swtab(range, swhdr, sw_array[0].clabel, 1),
2589 sw_array[0].clabel);
2590 chk_block(ilix);
2591 if (ILT_ILIP(expb.curilt) != ilix) {
2592 /*
2593 * An ILT was not created for the JMPM -- the previous ILT is an
2594 * unconditional branch. go through and decrement all of the
2595 * use counts for the switch labels
2596 */
2597 RFCNTD(sw_array[0].clabel);
2598 for (i = lb; i <= ub; i++)
2599 RFCNTD(sw_array[i].clabel);
2600 wr_block(); /* end this ilt block */
2601 }
2602 } else if (ncases > 4) {
2603 int m, first;
2604 SPTR label;
2605 /*
2606 * perform a binary search of the switch array:
2607 * generate ili of the form
2608 *
2609 * if (sw_val > sw_array[m].val) goto label;
2610 * switch for table[lb .. m]
2611 * label:
2612 * switch for table[m+1 .. ub]
2613 *
2614 * Note that a new block must be created for the switch on the
2615 * upper half of the table; the switch value must be temp stored
2616 * in the current block.
2617 */
2618 RFCNTI(sw_array[0].clabel); /* default label has another use */
2619 m = (lb + ub) / 2;
2620 if (sw_temp == 0) {
2621 int nme;
2622 /*
2623 * need to temp store the switch value in this block, and the
2624 * first use will be a cse of the original value
2625 */
2626 const SPTR sym = mkrtemp_sc(sw_val, expb.sc);
2627 sw_temp = ad_acon(sym, 0);
2628 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, sym, 0, 0);
2629 chk_block(ad4ili(IL_ST, sw_val, sw_temp, nme, MSZ_WORD));
2630 first = ad1ili(IL_CSEIR, sw_val);
2631 sw_val = ad3ili(IL_LD, sw_temp, nme, MSZ_WORD);
2632 } else /* use the load of the temporary containing the switch value */
2633 first = sw_val;
2634 label = getlab();
2635 RFCNTI(label);
2636 chk_block(ad4ili(IL_ICJMP, first, ad_icon(sw_array[m].val), 6, label));
2637 genswitch(lb, m);
2638 exp_label(label);
2639 genswitch(m + 1, ub);
2640 } else {
2641 int first, next, i;
2642 /*
2643 * generate a sequence of "if (sw_val == case value) goto case label"
2644 * followed by a JMP to the default label.
2645 */
2646 if (sw_temp) {
2647 /*
2648 * since the switch value has been temp stored, use the load
2649 * of the temp for all cases.
2650 */
2651 first = next = sw_val;
2652 } else if (ncases > 1 && flg.opt != 1) {
2653 /*
2654 * for this situation, the switch will generate multiple blocks.
2655 * Therefore, in the block evaluating sw_val, a temp store of
2656 * sw_val must occur and in ensuing blocks, the switch expression
2657 * will be fetched from the temporary.
2658 */
2659 int nme;
2660 const SPTR sym = mkrtemp_sc(sw_val, expb.sc);
2661 sw_temp = ad_acon(sym, 0);
2662 nme = addnme(NT_VAR, sym, 0, 0);
2663 chk_block(ad4ili(IL_ST, sw_val, sw_temp, nme, MSZ_WORD));
2664 /*
2665 * The first case occurs in the same block as the store, so just
2666 * use a cse of the original switch value for the first case.
2667 */
2668 first = ad1ili(IL_CSEIR, sw_val);
2669 next = sw_val = ad3ili(IL_LD, sw_temp, nme, MSZ_WORD);
2670 } else {
2671 /*
2672 * Since all of the conditional branches will fit in the current
2673 * block, the first branch uses sw_val and subsequent branches
2674 * will use a cse of sw_val.
2675 */
2676 first = sw_val;
2677 next = ad1ili(IL_CSEIR, sw_val);
2678 }
2679
2680 /* generate first compare */
2681
2682 chk_block(ad4ili(IL_ICJMP, first, ad_icon(sw_array[lb].val), 1,
2683 sw_array[lb].clabel));
2684
2685 /* generate compares for the remaining cases */
2686
2687 for (i = lb + 1; i <= ub; i++) {
2688 chk_block(ad4ili(IL_ICJMP, next, ad_icon(sw_array[i].val), 1,
2689 sw_array[i].clabel));
2690 }
2691
2692 /* generate the default jump */
2693
2694 chk_block(ad1ili(IL_JMP, sw_array[0].clabel));
2695 }
2696}
2697
2698static int agotostart;
2699
2700void
2701exp_build_agoto(int *tab, int mx)
2702{
2703 int i;
2704 SWEL *swelp;
2705
2706 if (mx <= 0)
2707 return;
2708 /*
2709 * AGOTOs will be treated like CGOTOs so an extra entry in the
2710 * switch table is needed for te default label.
2711 */
2712 agotostart = getswel(mx + 1);
2713 /*
2714 * switch_base[agotostart].clabel is reserved for the default
2715 */
2716 switch_base[agotostart].val = mx;
2717 switch_base[agotostart].next = agotostart + 1;
2718 swelp = 0; /* quite possible use before def */
2719 for (i = 1; i <= mx; i++) {
2720 swelp = switch_base + (agotostart + i);
2721 swelp->clabel = convertSPTR(tab[i - 1]);
2722 RFCNTI(swelp->clabel);
2723 swelp->val = i;
2724 swelp->next = (agotostart + i + 1);
2725 }
2726 swelp->next = 0;
2727}
2728
2729/** \brief Expand a goto
2730 *
2731 * for TARGET_LLVM, we are not performing an indirect branch, so expand
2732 * an assigned goto into a computed goto -- the labels appearing in the
2733 * ASSIGN statements and their respective computed goto index values have
2734 * already been collected into a switch_base table whose starting index
2735 * is agotostart.
2736 */
2737void
2738exp_agoto(ILM *ilmp, int curilm)
2739{
2740 INT i;
2741 INT n; /* # of cases */
2742
2743 sw_val = kimove(ILI_OF(ILM_OPND(ilmp, 2)));
2744 sw_temp = 0;
2745 i = agotostart; /* index from switch_base locating default */
2746 sw_array = switch_base + i;
2747 n = sw_array[0].val;
2748 sw_array[0].clabel = getlab();
2749 RFCNTI(sw_array[0].clabel);
2750#if DEBUG
2751 if (flg.dbg[10] != 0) {
2752 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil,
2753 "\n\n Switch: %-5d line: %-5d n: %-5d default: %-5d\n", curilm,
2754 gbl.lineno, n, sw_array[0].clabel);
2755 for (i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
2756 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " %10d %5d~\n", sw_array[i].val,
2757 sw_array[i].clabel);
2758 }
2759 }
2760#endif
2761 assert(n != 0, "exp_agoto: cnt is zero, at ilm", curilm, ERR_Severe);
2762 genswitch(1, n);
2763 exp_label(sw_array[0].clabel);
2764}

2940static void

2942{

2951
2952int
2953gen_arg_ili(void)
2954{
2955 ainfo_t ainfo;
2956 int i;
2957
2958 init_ainfo(&ainfo);
2959
2960 if (charargs > 0 && !HAS_OPT_ARGSG(exp_call_sym))
2961 process_desc_args(&ainfo);
2962
2963 /* go through the list of character length ili which have been
2964 * saved up and add them as arguments to the call.
2965 */
2966 for (i = charargs - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
2967 arg_charlen(len_ili[i], &ainfo);
2968 }
2969
2970 /* now go through the list of all stored arguments and add them
2971 * to the argument chain for this call
2972 */
2973 for (i = arg_entry - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
2974 int ili = arg_ili[i].ili_arg;
2975 if (charargs > 0 && !HAS_OPT_ARGSG(exp_call_sym) && is_proc_desc_arg(ili))
2976 continue;
2977 put_arg_ili(i, &ainfo);
2978 }
2979
2980 end_ainfo(&ainfo);
2981 return ainfo.lnk;
2982} /* gen_arg_ili */
